cc:Work.dc:title: Misc - TCGStorageBox
cc:Work.dc:description:
One big box for storing cards from trading card games or other deckbuilding game. (The picture sample is one I made for aeon's end
Adding '0:' at the start of the sy parameter adds a slot at the very back. Adding ':0' at the end of sy adds a slot meeting the bottom at the very front. This is especially useful if slot angle is set above zero.
There are 4 different sets of dividers rendered:
* With asymmetric tabs so the tabs fit on top of each other * With tabs of half wall thickness that can go side by side * With tabs of a full wall thickness * One single divider spanning across all columns
You will likely need to cut each of the dividers you want multiple times.
Some reworking is still to be made for allowing a different thickness for the inside wall For estetique improuvement we need to allow the possibilitty to made a "outside" box
Created with Boxes.py (https://boxes.hackerspace-bamberg.de/) Command line: boxes TCGStorageBox Command line short: boxes TCGStorageBox
